----------------
Running miramare
----------------

1) Download the dust template by running:

bash getTestData.sh

2) Run the component separation pipeline. e.g.

./run_compsep parfiles/testsim_perturb.par

3) Once the pipeline is run, components are found in the output/
directory. The foreground parameter likelihoods can be inspected by
running:

sm < output/testsim_perturb.sm
gv output/testsim_perturb.ps

or using by matlab to run the output/*.m scripts.
